The paper deals with a query problem related to trajectory data, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for filtering and refining the results, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of reverse k nearest neighbor search is a well-studied problem in computational geometry and data structures (cs.DS), and the paper proposes a new index structure to handle dynamic updates. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on real datasets, which suggests that the work may also be relevant to the machine learning community (cs.LG).
